<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 04 at 4:29PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Warren,
east central Greene, Taliaferro and southwestern Wilkes Counties
through 500 PM EDT...
At 429 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Lyneville, or near
Crawfordville, moving south at 20 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Crawfordville, Union Point, White Plains, Siloam, Sharon, Barnett,
Robinson, Lyneville, Alexander Stephens Park, Sandy Cross, Carters
Grove and Daniel Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
